- +# PR Analysis & Description Generation
- +## Goal
- +Analyze only branch-owned changes (excluding merge-from-`dev` noise) and produce a concise, systematic PR description with clear **how** and **why**.
- +## Non-Negotiables
- +1. Compare against `dev` by default unless explicitly overridden.
  +2. Exclude merge commits and merged `dev` history from analysis.
  +3. Output PR description inside a copy-ready markdown fence: ` ```markdown `.
  +4. Do not include any testing steps/checklists.
  +5. Mention changed files only once, in a final `Changed Files Index` section.
  +6. Keep content concise; omit non-essential narrative.
- +## Merge-Noise Exclusion Strategy
- +Use merge-base and cherry-aware commit filtering:
- +```bash
  +# Base for branch-owned diff
  +BASE="$(git merge-base HEAD dev)"
- +# Unique non-merge commits on current branch (excludes merged dev commits)
  +git log --cherry-pick --right-only --no-merges --oneline dev...HEAD
- +# File-level and line-level changes for branch-owned work only
  +git diff --name-status "$BASE"..HEAD
+git diff --stat "$BASE"..HEAD
  +```
- +## Analysis Workflow
- +### 1) Collect Source Data
- +`bash
+BASE="$(git merge-base HEAD dev)"
+git branch --show-current
+git log --cherry-pick --right-only --no-merges --oneline dev...HEAD
+git diff --stat "$BASE"..HEAD
+git diff --name-status "$BASE"..HEAD
+`
- +Optional deep dive:
- +`bash
+git diff "$BASE"..HEAD -- path/to/file.ts
+`
- +### 2) Categorize Changes
- +Use only these sections when relevant:
- +- `Fixes`
  +- `Features`
  +- `Improvements`
  +- `Breaking Changes` (only if applicable)
  +- `Chores` (only if meaningful)
- +Each bullet must explain:
- +- **What changed** (implementation)
  +- **Why it changed** (problem/goal)
- +Do not repeat file paths inside these sections.
- +### 3) Generate Output
- +Return exactly one copy-ready block:
- +``markdown
+`markdown
  +# <conventional-commit-style title>
- +## Overview
  +- <1-2 bullets summarizing scope and intent>
- +## Changes Summary
  +- **Total Files Changed**: <number>
  +- **Lines Added**: +<number>
  +- **Lines Removed**: -<number>
  +- **Commits**: <number>
- +## Fixes
  +- <what changed + why>
- +## Features
  +- <what changed + why>
- +## Improvements
  +- <what changed + why>
- +## Breaking Changes
  +- <only if applicable; otherwise omit section>
- +## Chores
  +- <only if meaningful; otherwise omit section>
- +## Changed Files Index
  +- `<path/to/file-a>`
  +- `<path/to/file-b>`
  +- `<path/to/file-c>`
  +```
  +````
- +## Quality Bar
- +1. No testing sections anywhere.
  +2. No reviewer checklist.
  +3. No screenshots/demo placeholders unless user explicitly asks.
  +4. No redundant sections.
  +5. `Changed Files Index` appears once, at the end only.
- +## Suggested Commands
- +`bash
+# Counts for summary
+BASE="$(git merge-base HEAD dev)"
+git diff --shortstat "$BASE"..HEAD
+git diff --name-only "$BASE"..HEAD | wc -l
+git log --cherry-pick --right-only --no-merges --oneline dev...HEAD | wc -l
+`
- +## Example Command Flow
- +`bash
+BASE="$(git merge-base HEAD dev)"
+git log --cherry-pick --right-only --no-merges --oneline dev...HEAD
+git diff --stat "$BASE"..HEAD
+git diff --name-status "$BASE"..HEAD
+`
